# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — written 2026-05-12 (S34 hygiene)
#
# Philosophy:
#   - Source code (.cpp .hpp .py .sh .md) is NEVER ignored except for a few
#     explicitly-listed operator helper scripts.
#   - Everything else — built binaries, sweep outputs, market-data captures,
#     logs, archives, OS junk — is ignored.
#   - Already-tracked files (e.g. data/l2_ticks_2026-04-16.csv) keep being
#     tracked; .gitignore only affects future `git add` of new files.
# =============================================================================

# ── SECRETS — never commit ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.github_token
.env
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
secrets/

# ── OS / editor junk ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.vscode/
.idea/

# ── Archives / installers ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.zip
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.dmg
*.iso
Omega-main.zip
Claude.dmg
FIX-4.4-Specification-with-20030618-Errata-44775/
FIX-4.4-Specification-with-20030618-Errata-44775.zip

# ── Build artifacts ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
build/
*.o
*.obj
*.a
*.so
*.dylib
*.exe
*.gch
*.pch
include/version_generated.hpp

# ── Python caches ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.venv/
venv/
.pytest_cache/

# ── Logs / inspection / run outputs ───────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
*.out
/inspect_c*.out
/run_*.log
/cfe_post_*.log
/hbg_post_*.log

# ── Runtime log directory (VPS-side; should never be committed) ───────────────
# Source of the 2026-05-29 git pull failure: omega_shadow.csv was tracked
# and held open by the running Omega.exe service. Add the whole logs/ tree
# to .gitignore so future pulls never collide on a runtime file write.
# Tracked-already files (none after the cleanup commit) remain tracked.
logs/
data/ibkr_l2/
data/trades.ndjson
state/

# ── Pre-S86 / pre-dispatch-fix exe + config backups (operator-side, big) ──────
